Step 2: Enable the Sysctl ParametersOnce the module is active, the paths are generated. Run the following commands to configure iptables to see bridged traffic:bashsudo sysctl net.bridge.bridge-nf-call-iptables=1
sudo sysctl net.bridge.bridge-nf-call-ip6tables=1
sudo sysctl net.ipv4.ip_forward=1
Use code with caution.
Step 3: Make the Changes PersistentTo ensure this configuration survives a system reboot, you must save it to your system configuration files.Persist the module load by creating a configuration file:bashecho "br_netfilter" | sudo tee /etc/modules-load.d/k8s.conf
Use code with caution.Persist the network settings by creating a system control layout:bashcat <<EOF | sudo tee /etc/sysctl.d/k8s.conf
net.bridge.bridge-nf-call-iptables = 1
net.bridge.bridge-nf-call-ip6tables = 1
net.ipv4.ip_forward = 1
EOF
